            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Just in case you are not aware (although you should be before opening such a pull request): The issue is queries, which are guaranteed to be compatible with only a specific parser version (sometimes even commit). And queries are (necessarily) editor-specific, so these are part of our runtime and not able to be outsourced to system packages, just like syntax files. This implies that we _need_ to have full control over which parsers are used. This implies that parsers are also to be considered as part of our runtime and not to be shared with other editors (which may need a _different_ version -- or even parser if multiple forks exist).\r\n\r\nTL;DR: System-wide parsers are just asking for pain; no way are we going to support that.\r\n\r\n> This directory is symlinked to /usr/share/nvim/runtime/parser\r\n\r\n**openSUSE should not be doing this at all.** I cannot stress enough how bad of an idea that is.",
