            "body": "Parser and editors are all built against the same runtime and parser versions.\r\nThe parsers built by Neovim are the same parsers built in the openSUSE packaging.\r\nThere isn't any interference into the prebuilds shipped by Neovim, this is about distribution packaging of tree-sitter parser as already done by other distributions.\r\n\r\n> Just in case you are not aware (although you should be before opening such a pull request): The issue is queries, which are guaranteed to be compatible with only a specific parser version (sometimes even commit).\r\n\r\nSource to that? If tree-sitter is that unstable who is it even suitable for production use?",
